==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Dura mater
<hw>Du"ra ma"ter</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[L., lit., hard mother. The
membrane was called <ets>mater</ets>, or mother, because it was formerly
thought to give rise to every membrane of the body.]</ety>
<fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>The tough, fibrous membrane, which lines the
cavity of the skull and spinal column, and surrounds the brain and
spinal cord; -- frequently abbreviated to <abbr>dura</abbr>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Duramen</ent>⟦br⟧
